Came here and sat outside during COVID. We just had the wine, but the server was attentive and super friendly, and the drinks were great too. I'll be back soon!
Great $5 wine happy hour and great french onion soup.

Mixed review - have been served here twice love it, is a nice neighborhood bar, with desserts... blocks from my house.  But they have a soft close policy - they close when they want to.  Twice I have entered the open door not very late in the evening and been turned away - people in the bar, early evening... say hey we’re closing soon - we can serve you, but we’re closed... one and done, which is better than a hard no!  25° F - I walk several blocks to get to you for a wine and perhaps a crepe... Don’t turn me away... Maxwells, Zeppelins, Chaplin’s... are happy to stay open published hours and take my money.

La Jambe was a really lovely French spot in Shaw. I visited for happy hour and enjoyed some wine with a charcuterie board. The service was brief but kind. The space was comfortable and cozy while the prices were in line with what we expected. I’d for sure visit again!

Great little wine bar located in Shaw offering French  wines and cheese. We came here for pre dinner drinks and really enjoyed the atmosphere and the wine, we got a cheese board as an appetizer and had a great time hanging out at the bar. It’s a little pricy compared to some wine bars and they lack some cheaper options, but it’s really hard to beat the location. I’d definitely like to try it again in the future.
A great little wine bar

I love this place.  It’s rare to find a restaurant in DC that feels “homey” and inviting, relaxed. La Jambe feels more like a restaurant in a small French city than one in the middle of Washington.  The bartenders are friendly and great at their job, and the cocktails and food are excellent and keep me coming back.

We will be back! Grilled cheese and tomato soup was a great dish to split, especially paired with a crisp white wine that their knowledgable staff can tell you plenty about! Want to try everything on the menu especially the raclette!
I like this place but the last time I went the coffee was bad and the service was awful.

Fun atmosphere but very mediocre wines at best. Reds are served warm (not at proper temperature). Acidity, fruit, tannin balance lends me to believe these are very cheaply produced. With a couple exceptions, these taste nothing like French wines. The food is descent, but I wouldn’t recommend this place based on wines.
Haven’t ever been but it’s called ‘leg’ in French and that’s worth something
I love this place !! Maybe because I’m French ?? 😛. Good selection of cheese, ham and wine. Have a seat at the bar and don’t hesitate to engage with the bar tenders, they are super nice.

Before dinner, my boyfriend and I decided to grab cocktails at La Jambe, a wine bar in the Logan Circle area. Our bartender Josael showed off his skills in making handcrafted cocktails.  I convinced my boyfriend to try a cocktail with wine instead of ordering a glass of wine. My boyfriend enjoyed the Le Serpent cocktail, which consisted of fruit brandy, honey syrup, shrub, pineapple allspice, fresh lime, pineapple habanero bitters, and french sparkling wine.  I enjoyed the Southside Rose, which consisted of citadelle gin, rose syrup, fresh lime, fresh mint, angostura bitters, and grapefruit bitters. Despite not being a fan of gin, I actually liked this drink because it was fruity, sweet, and quite refreshing.
Went there for a Miami University Alumni event.  Great wine!
Great Service and tasty drinks. We had the rosé and  old fashion.
Great service on a fancy but approachable list. Sit at the bar for special attention, which isn't really special, but easier to chat about what to have next.
Very knowledgeable and attentive bartender Dave. Yummy cocktails and tasty Rhum and Whisky flights. Clean and comfortable place to sip.
Great cocktails and wine selection. The food is also spot on. Highly recommend.
Friendly, knowledgable staff. They make delicious food, have a large French wine selection and create incredible seasonal cocktails. If you can, get the grilled cheese and tomato soup.
Cute place and good food. I just wish the stools were a little more comfortable.
Wine, ambiance, service, affordability. Fantastic across all measures for an establishment like this.

Went for a private event and was able to sample a lot of the food. Very authentic french. High quality and very nice ambiance. The charcuterie and cheese place was to die for and the wine list offered fantastic wines at modest prices. Will go again.

Had a really lovely evening here catching up with a friend. Wine selection was great, we enjoyed all the food we ordered (especially the chef’s choice charcuterie board), and the service was lovely. Would definitely come back and recommend to anyone looking for a quiet evening in Shaw.
Great service and nice wine selection.  Good happy hour prices.  Very good places to hang out for a drink.
Stopped by for a drink and a plate of olives. Lovely elegant atmosphere and great service.
Cute little wine bar in the heart of Shaw. Staff is welcoming and helpful. The biggest complaint is that the food offerings are limited (it has something to do with the space).

Brunch here was really good.  The staff was helpful and nice and the food was really good! I ordered the croque madame and the baguette French toast.  The sweet crepe option was OK but everything else was really tasty.  I love that they make a lot of their sauces and dressings in house
Amazing wine selction and the owners are very friendly and down to earth.

Mediocre and expensive. The wine is good, but poured in micro servings, the cheeses did not travel well and took a taste of ammonia, and cold cuts were just average. The bill was not. You can pass your way.
Nice quiet bar with reasonable selection.
Always a great stop for something tasty and special creations from the bar staff. Definitely worth it.

Brought some friends here for brunch and had a great experience.  Food was great and we all really enjoyed La Boutielle.  My only complaint is that the poor place isn't getting enough customers.  Come on, folks!
Cool spot. You could almost walk by without noticing but worth the stop for some great fromage & charcuterie.  Also interesting salads, warm dishes and entrees. Excellent wine list. Nice people.

It is definitely one of the hidden gems in the city! Highly recommended....nice design, positive atmosphere, attentive personnel and interesting wines offered by the glass! Also, there is a special room for wine testing. A modern French place, the intimate and energetic space out of Paris.

Fantastic place to grab a light bite and some fantastic French wine. The wait staff is incredibly knowledgeable and helps you narrow down their wide selection of wine to match your taste preference.  Definitely worth a visit. And once you go, you'll want to return.
